 open-e-joviandss-proxmox-plugin (0.11.2-0) stable; urgency=medium

    * New: Per-VM concurrent locking (OpenEJovianDSS/Lock.pm) — replaces
      storage-wide lock with fine-grained per-VM locks; concurrent operations
      on different VMs no longer block each other
    * New: Cluster-wide lock via pmxcfs atomic mkdir for shared storage;
      node-local flock for non-shared storage
    * New: Dual per-VM locking in clone_image (ordered by vmid) to prevent
      deadlock when source and destination VMs differ
    * New: 8-character hex request ID (reqid) in all debug log lines for
      per-operation log correlation
    * New: udev rule 50-joviandss-scsi-skip-dm.rules to prevent kernel
      scanning of JovianDSS device-mapper devices as raw SCSI disks
    * Fix: NFS plugin crash "JovianDSS data addresses are not provided" —
      NFSCommon.pm updated for $ctx refactoring in Common.pm
    * Fix: iSCSI target deletion now re-checks target presence to ensure
      complete removal before returning
    * Fix: rescan-scsi-bus.sh timeout no longer aborts the scan loop;
      error is logged and iteration continues
    * Fix: Remove trailing comma in rest.py that caused malformed REST requests
    * Fix: Remove recursive snapshot flag for NAS volumes to prevent
      unintended child dataset snapshots
    * Fix: apt-get --reinstall and --allow-downgrades moved after 'install'
      subcommand in install.pl

